ins how and why apparently inconsequential territories become central to national discourse in Japan, South Korea, and Taiwan. These Islands Are Ours challenges the conventional wisdom that disputes-related campaigns originate in the desire to protect national territory and traces their roots to times of crisis in the respective societies. This book gives us a new way to understand the nature of territorial disputes and how they inform national identities by exploring the processes of their social construction, and amplification.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aNationalismzEast Asia. 0aTerritory, NationalxSocial aspectszEast Asia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh  aDiaoyutai.  aDokdo.  aNortheast Asia.  aNorthern Territories.  aSenkaku Islands.  aSocial Constructivism.  aTakeshima.  anationalism.  anon-state actors.  aterritorial disputes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503611900zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611900.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyte